Your Vault has a 2-step Unlock and Spend process to transfer from it
and there is a mandatory yet configureable delay enforced between these
Unlock and Spend Transactions for every private-key/combination allowed
to spend from this Vault.
-------------
Press any key to configure these delays and continue...
[H[2J[3J
-------------
Lets configure the on-chain delay / cooling period
for spending with your private-key from your Vault!

This will give you time to react and initiate recovery
when your private-key or wallet backup (seed phrase) is stolen
and is used to unlock and potentially spend from your Vault.
-------------
Enter delay in blocks or press [Return] to use default [1000]: Setting Option 1 (User Private-Key Only) Delay to 1000
Encoded bytes (hex): e803
[H[2J[3J
-------------
Now, lets configure the on-chain delay / cooling period
for spending with the Sentinel private-key from your Vault!

This is the delay your Sentinel has to wait before he can
transfer/recover from your Vault in case your private-key
is lost or for managing your inheritance.

PS: This is typically much longer than the previously set delay
and will give you time to react and override any spend attempt
by compromised/rogue Sentinels with just your private-key
eliminating counter-party risk in the Hybrid Custody Ecosystem.
-------------
Enter delay in blocks or press [Return] to use default [5000]: Setting Option 2 (Sentinel Private-Key Only) Delay to 5000
Encoded bytes (hex): 8813
[H[2J[3J
-------------
Now, lets configure the Recovery Address for your Vault!

Once your private-keys are lost or stolen, it is not
safe to recover your Vault to an address controlled by you
as we never know how deep the compromise is.

The best approach would be to temporarily transfer the coins in your
Vault to a custodial wallet address (Coinbase, Binance, etc.) and disable
withdrawls from it until you can create a new secure cold-storage wallet and Vault.

Alternatively, you can setup a new unused Hardware Wallet
with a new seed-phrase and store both the hardware wallet and
seed-phrase backup in a bank locker and use this wallet's address as Recovery Address!

PS: Sentinels are bound by on-chain Staking/Slashing mechanics
to only sign Recovery transactions to this Preconfigured Recovery Address
as no user provided input can be trusted post compromise/setup!
-------------
Enter Recovery Address or press [Return] to use default [bcrt1qmsllunzg7enp0vs6g2vpmmfp9fvyw8zlrd2e2c]: Proceeding with Recovery Address: bcrt1qmsllunzg7enp0vs6g2vpmmfp9fvyw8zlrd2e2c
